#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.62"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.62:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.62:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 62. Dutiyaassutavāsutta → dutiyaassutavantusuttaṃ (bj) | assutavā (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.62:0.3"
msgid "62. Dutiyaassutavāsutta"
msgstr "62. Uneducated (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.96"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.62:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano imasmiṃ cātumahābhūtikasmiṃ kāyasmiṃ "
"nibbindeyyapi virajjeyyapi vimucceyyapi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when it comes to this body made up of the four primary "
"elements, an uneducated ordinary person might become disillusioned, "
"dispassionate, and freed."

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.4"
msgid ""
"Dissati, bhikkhave, imassa cātumahābhūtikassa kāyassa ācayopi apacayopi "
"ādānampi nikkhepanampi."
msgstr ""
"This body made up of the four primary elements is seen to increase and "
"diminish, to be taken up and laid to rest."

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.5"
msgid "Tasmā tatrāssutavā puthujjano nibbindeyyapi virajjeyyapi vimucceyyapi."
msgstr ""
"That’s why, when it comes to this body, an uneducated ordinary person might "
"become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed."

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.6"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, vuccati cittaṃ itipi, mano itipi, viññāṇaṃ itipi, "
"tatrāssutavā puthujjano nālaṃ nibbindituṃ nālaṃ virajjituṃ nālaṃ vimuccituṃ."
msgstr ""
"But when it comes to that which is called ‘mind’ or ‘sentience’ or "
"‘consciousness’, an uneducated ordinary person is unable to become "
"disillusioned, dispassionate, or freed."

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.8"
msgid ""
"Dīgharattañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, assutavato puthujjanassa ajjhositaṃ mamāyitaṃ "
"parāmaṭṭhaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Because for a long time they’ve been attached to it, thought of it as their "
"own, and mistaken it:"

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.9"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti."
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’"

msgctxt "sn12.62:1.10"
msgid ""
"Tasmā tatrāssutavā puthujjano nālaṃ nibbindituṃ nālaṃ virajjituṃ nālaṃ "
"vimuccituṃ."
msgstr ""
"That’s why, when it comes to this mind, an uneducated ordinary person is "
"unable to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.62:2.1"
msgid ""
"Varaṃ, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano imaṃ cātumahābhūtikaṃ kāyaṃ attato "
"upagaccheyya, na tveva cittaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But an uneducated ordinary person would be better off taking this body made "
"up of the four primary elements to be their self, rather than the mind."

msgctxt "sn12.62:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn12.62:2.3"
msgid ""
"Dissatāyaṃ, bhikkhave, cātumahābhūtiko kāyo ekampi vassaṃ tiṭṭhamāno dvepi "
"vassāni tiṭṭhamāno tīṇipi vassāni tiṭṭhamāno cattāripi vassāni tiṭṭhamāno "
"pañcapi vassāni tiṭṭhamāno dasapi vassāni tiṭṭhamāno vīsatipi vassāni "
"tiṭṭhamāno tiṃsampi vassāni tiṭṭhamāno cattārīsampi vassāni tiṭṭhamāno "
"paññāsampi vassāni tiṭṭhamāno vassasatampi tiṭṭhamāno, bhiyyopi tiṭṭhamāno."
msgstr ""
"This body made up of the four primary elements is seen to last for a year, "
"or for two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, or a "
"hundred years, or even longer."

msgctxt "sn12.62:2.4"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, vuccati cittaṃ itipi, mano itipi, viññāṇaṃ itipi, "
"taṃ rattiyā ca divasassa ca aññadeva uppajjati aññaṃ nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"But that which is called ‘mind’ or ‘sentience’ or ‘consciousness’ arises as "
"one thing and ceases as another all day and all night."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.97"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.62:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako paṭiccasamuppādaṃyeva sādhukaṃ yoniso "
"manasi karoti:"
msgstr ""
"In this case, a learned noble disciple carefully and properly attends to "
"dependent origination itself:"

msgctxt "sn12.62:3.2"
msgid "‘iti imasmiṃ sati idaṃ hoti, imassuppādā idaṃ uppajjati;"
msgstr "‘When this exists, that is; due to the arising of this, that arises."

msgctxt "sn12.62:3.3"
msgid "imasmiṃ asati idaṃ na hoti, imassa nirodhā idaṃ nirujjhatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"When this doesn’t exist, that is not; due to the cessation of this, that "
"ceases. That is:"

msgctxt "sn12.62:3.4"
msgid "Sukhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhavedanā."
msgstr ""
"Pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant."

msgctxt "sn12.62:3.5"
msgid ""
"Tasseva sukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"sukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā sukhavedanā sā nirujjhati sā "
"vūpasammati."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as pleasant, the "
"corresponding pleasant feeling ceases and stops."

msgctxt "sn12.62:3.6"
msgid "Dukkhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhavedanā."
msgstr ""
"Painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful."

msgctxt "sn12.62:3.7"
msgid ""
"Tasseva dukkhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"dukkhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā dukkhavedanā sā nirujjhati sā "
"vūpasammati."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as painful, the "
"corresponding painful feeling ceases and stops."

msgctxt "sn12.62:3.8"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ, bhikkhave, phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"adukkhamasukhavedanā."
msgstr ""
"Neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral."

msgctxt "sn12.62:3.9"
msgid ""
"Tasseva adukkhamasukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā adukkhamasukhavedanā sā "
"nirujjhati sā vūpasammati."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as neutral, the "
"corresponding neutral feeling ceases and stops."

# See BB’s note for variants.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.62:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dvinnaṃ kaṭṭhānaṃ saṅghaṭṭanasamodhānā usmā jāyati "
"tejo abhinibbattati. Tesaṃyeva dvinnaṃ kaṭṭhānaṃ nānākatavinibbhogā yā tajjā "
"usmā sā nirujjhati sā vūpasammati;"
msgstr ""
"When you rub two sticks together, heat is generated and fire is produced. "
"But when you part the sticks and lay them aside, any corresponding heat "
"ceases and stops."

msgctxt "sn12.62:4.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, sukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhavedanā."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be "
"experienced as pleasant."

# The pe in MS appears to be unnecessary here.
msgctxt "sn12.62:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tasseva sukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"sukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā sukhavedanā sā nirujjhati sā "
"vūpasammati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as pleasant, the "
"corresponding pleasant feeling ceases and stops."

msgctxt "sn12.62:4.4"
msgid "dukkhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca …"
msgstr "Painful feeling …"

msgctxt "sn12.62:4.5"
msgid "adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhavedanā."
msgstr ""
"Neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral."

msgctxt "sn12.62:4.6"
msgid ""
"Tasseva adukkhamasukhavedaniyassa phassassa nirodhā yaṃ tajjaṃ vedayitaṃ "
"adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā adukkhamasukhavedanā sā "
"nirujjhati sā vūpasammati."
msgstr ""
"With the cessation of that contact to be experienced as neutral, the "
"corresponding neutral feeling ceases and stops."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.62:5.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako phassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi "
"nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi "
"nibbindati;"
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, "
"feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.62:5.2"
msgid ""
"nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati, vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn12.62:5.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.62:5.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
